- how is risk measured, net present value, 8% discount rate.
- different for different actors.
For investors, it is the difference in the value of assets. The value of assets is calculated as ... the net present value is then calculated as the difference between the value  of ... and ...

For government, as a shareholder the same, and as a tax collector, the difference between the income obtianed
For workers and households, it is the difference between income under both scenarios.
